1
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:11,291
- YOU FEELING OKAY, GRAMPS?

2
00:00:11,375 --> 00:00:13,833
- WE THOUGHT THE DOCTOR CLEARED
YOU TO LEAVE THE HOSPITAL

3
00:00:13,916 --> 00:00:15,833
- I'VE BEEN PUTTING OFF
TELLING YOU TWO,

4
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:18,708
BUT MY CONDITION IS MUCH MORE
SERIOUS THAN WE THOUGHT.

5
00:00:18,791 --> 00:00:20,291
THE DOCTOR HAS TOLD ME

6
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:22,791
I'M GOING TO NEED TO
STAY HERE MUCH LONGER.

7
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:23,833
- I HOPE THIS "CONDITION"

8
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,458
DOESN'T INVOLVE
GIRLS IN WHITE HATS.

9
00:00:25,541 --> 00:00:27,958
- I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT YOU MEAN.

10
00:00:28,041 --> 00:00:30,083
- COME ON, GRAMPS, DID
YOU REALLY HAVE TO MOVE

11
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:33,500
INTO A PRIVATE VIP SUITE?
THESE ROOMS ARE EXPENSIVE.

12
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:35,000
HOW ARE YOU SUPPOSED
TO PAY FOR IT?

13
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:37,291
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME YOU'RE
AUCTIONING THE HOUSE.

14
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:38,541
- DON'T WORRY, KOUHEI,

15
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:40,458
I HAD A LOVELY CHAT WITH
THE BILLING DEPARTMENT

16
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,500
AND I CONVINCED THEM TO
GIVE ME A SPECIAL RATE

17
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:44,708
WITH SOME HELP FROM MY
SECRET HYPNOSIS POTION.

18
00:00:44,791 --> 00:00:48,416
( laughing )

19
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,666
- IT'S A GOOD THING YOU WEREN'T
MORE AMBITIOUS IN LIFE.

20
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:55,750
- ( theme song playing )

21
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:58,125
- ( singing in Japanese )

22
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,875
- Kouhei: ANY NEWS ON KINKEL?
- Seiji: NOTHING YET.

23
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,750
- ( sighs )

24
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:31,208
IF WE COULD JUST FIND ELFRIEDE,

25
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:33,375
WE'D BE AT LEAST ONE STEP
CLOSER TO FINDING THE COUNT.

26
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:35,250
- SHE'S THE HELPFUL
VAMPIRE, RIGHT?

27
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:51,375
- ( chuckling )

28
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,666
- ( knock on door )

29
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,125
- COME IN. THE DOOR'S OPEN.

30
00:02:59,166 --> 00:03:02,041
OH. DIDN'T EXPECT TO SEE YOU.

31
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,041
TOO BAD YOU DIDN'T STOP
BY A LITTLE EARLIER.

32
00:03:04,125 --> 00:03:05,583
YOU JUST MISSED
KOUHEI AND SEIJI.

33
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,958
I'M SURPRISED YOU DIDN'T
SEE THEM ON YOUR WAY UP.

34
00:03:08,041 --> 00:03:10,291
YOU'LL HAVE TO GIVE THEM A CALL
AND TELL THEM YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

35
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:11,791
THEY'RE PRETTY WORRIED.

36
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:13,916
THEY HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE TO
REACH YOU THESE PAST FEW DAYS.

37
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:23,416
- THAT'S WEIRD. DOOR'S OPEN.
I COULD HAVE SWORN I LOCKED IT.

38
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:25,958
- YOU CAN'T AFFORD TO MAKE
SUCH CARELESS MISTAKES, KOUHEI.

39
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:27,916
WE'RE IN ENOUGH DANGER AS IT IS.

40
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:32,250
- HMPH!

41
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,666
DIDN'T ANYONE EVER TEACH YOU

42
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,583
IT'S RUDE TO BE LATE WHEN
YOU HAVE A GUEST?

43
00:03:35,666 --> 00:03:37,791
- GUEST?
- THAT'S WHAT I SAID!

44
00:03:37,875 --> 00:03:40,833
AND SINCE YOU'VE NO CONCEPT
OF TIME AND MASTER IS SLEEPING,

45
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,166
I'VE BEEN KEEPING HIM COMPANY.

46
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:43,541
- OH, SORRY ABOUT THAT.

47
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,000
HEY, HAVE YOU GONE INSANE?

48
00:03:47,083 --> 00:03:48,000
YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO

49
00:03:48,083 --> 00:03:49,708
REVEAL YOURSELF
TO ANYONE BUT US!

50
00:03:57,375 --> 00:03:58,750
( gasps )

51
00:03:58,833 --> 00:03:59,791
- WELCOME BACK.

52
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
- HEY! IT'S THE EDITOR-IN-CHIEF!

53
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:05,125
WE'VE BEEN WORRYING
SICK ABOUT YOU, YOU KNOW THAT?

54
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:07,333
YOU COULD'VE AT LEAST
RETURNED OUR PHONE CALLS!

55
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:09,083
FOR ALL WE KNEW YOU
COULD HAVE BEEN INJURED

56
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,250
ON ONE OF YOUR
STORY ASSIGNMENTS.

57
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,000
EITHER THAT OR YOU
FINALLY CONVINCED HIROMI

58
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:14,083
TO RUN OFF WITH YOU
AND TIE THE KNOT.

59
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:15,708
- ARE YOU FINISHED?

60
00:04:15,791 --> 00:04:18,083
- HEY, DON'T PRETEND LIKE
YOU DON'T AGREE WITH ME!

61
00:04:18,166 --> 00:04:21,041
- KOUHEI, NOT ONLY DO YOU
HAVE THE SOCIAL GRACES

62
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:22,625
OF A BARNYARD ANIMAL,

63
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,125
YOU'VE SHOWN YOURSELF TO BE MORE
DENSE THAN I THOUGHT POSSIBLE.

64
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:26,458
- WHAT?

65
00:04:26,541 --> 00:04:28,208
- HAVEN'T YOU NOTICED
ANYTHING PECULIAR?

66
00:04:31,791 --> 00:04:33,875
- HEY! HE'S WEARING
GRANDPA'S WORK ROBE!

67
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:38,333
I DON'T GET IT, WHY IS THE
EDITOR IN GRANDPA'S CLOTHES?

68
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:40,000
- DO I REALLY HAVE TO
SPELL IT OUT FOR YOU?

69
00:04:44,791 --> 00:04:47,125
- NOW I SEE!
YOU HAVE GOT GRANDPA!

70
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:49,500
- WHY YES, I'M HAPPY TO
REPORT THAT YOUR GRANDFATHER

71
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:52,333
HAS BEEN IN MY MASTER'S
CUSTODY FOR QUITE SOME TIME.

72
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:53,916
( laughing )

73
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,708
- WHO'S HE TALKING ABOUT?
- MY GUESS IS COUNT KINKEL.

74
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:58,458
- UH-OH.

75
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:02,250
- IT SEEMS HE'S TURNED THIS
POOR MAN INTO ONE OF HIS SLAVES.

76
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,166
- SO DO YOU THINK THAT'S WHAT
HAPPENED TO HIROMI?

77
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,291
- MOST LIKELY.

78
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,375
- MY MASTER SENT ME TO DELIVER

79
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:12,875
AN INVITATION FOR YOU
TO JOIN HIM AT HIS ESTATE.

80
00:05:12,958 --> 00:05:14,500
ISN'T THAT WONDERFUL?

81
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:16,000
( laughing )

82
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,583
- ( lightning crashing )

83
00:05:20,791 --> 00:05:24,000
- Kouhei: THAT'S THE HOUSE THAT
HAZUKI GREW UP IN, ISN'T IT?

84
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:26,458
- Editor: KOUHEI MORIOKA,
SEIJI MIDO,

85
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:28,500
AND THE CHILD ARE
INVITED TO ATTEND.

86
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:32,333
IN ADDITION, MY MASTER WISHES
TO EXTEND A WARNING.

87
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:34,541
SHOULD ANY OF YOU
CHOOSE TO DECLINE,

88
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:37,416
YOU WILL DO SO AT THE COST
OF YOUR GRANDFATHER'S LIFE!

89
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,791
- HUH?

90
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:40,750
- ( laughing )

91
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,583
- FOR ALL WE KNOW GRANDPA'S
AT THE HOSPITAL

92
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:44,625
RIGHT WHERE WE LEFT HIM AND
THIS IS JUST SOME LOUSY TRAP!

93
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,375
- DOUBTFUL. KINKEL'S TOO STRONG
TO RELY ON EMPTY THREATS,

94
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:50,000
AND THAT MEANS
WE'RE IN REAL TROUBLE.

95
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:52,833
THE OTHER NIGHT, WHEN WE HAD TO
FACE THE COUNT AT THE HOTEL,

96
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,333
THE ONLY REASON
WE SUCCEEDED WAS

97
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:56,625
BECAUSE WE HAD GRANDFATHER
AND ELFRIEDE'S HELP.

98
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:58,875
BUT NOT THIS TIME.

99
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:00,875
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT? WE HAVE YOU!

100
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:02,416
THAT'S GOT TO COUNT
FOR SOMETHING, RIGHT?

101
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,875
- AS MUCH AS IT PAINS ME
TO ADMIT MY OWN SHORTCOMINGS,

102
00:06:04,958 --> 00:06:07,750
THERE'S NO FEASIBLE WAY I COULD
DEFEAT A VAMPIRE LIKE KINKEL.

103
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,416
I KNOW IT'S NOT WHAT
YOU WANT TO HEAR

104
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,958
BUT GOING THERE
MEANS CERTAIN DEATH.

105
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,833
I'M SORRY. BUT THIS
JUST LOOKS HOPELESS.

106
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:14,291
- Hazuki: WELL
I'M GOING, ANYWAY.

107
00:06:17,875 --> 00:06:19,791
I'LL GO ALONE IF I HAVE TO.

108
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:23,375
- YOU'RE AWAKE, MASTER.
- BUT YOU CAN'T GO!

109
00:06:23,458 --> 00:06:25,666
- GRANDFATHER HAS ALWAYS
BEEN SO NICE TO ME,

110
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,333
EVEN WHEN I DIDN'T DESERVE IT.

111
00:06:27,416 --> 00:06:31,458
HE'S SURE TREATED ME A HECK OF A
LOT BETTER THAN YOU TWO HAVE!

112
00:06:31,541 --> 00:06:34,125
HE GAVE ME HAIJI, AND HE GAVE
ME THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT

113
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:35,291
WHEN NOBODY ELSE WOULD.

114
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:36,333
- MMM-HMM.

115
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:42,416
SO I'M GOING. AND I PROMISE,
KINKEL WILL PAY!

116
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,333
- THAT'S NOT VERY POLITE,
LITTLE GIRL.

117
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:46,333
MY MASTER WILL
HAVE TO PUNISH YOU.

118
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:48,458
( laughing )

119
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:54,708
- WHAT'S HE LAUGHING AT?

120
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:56,958
- JUDGING FROM HIS BEHAVIOR, THE
COUNT HAS PROBABLY ORDERED HIM

121
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:59,458
TO LAUGH HIMSELF TO DEATH AFTER
HE CARRIED OUT HIS MISSION,

122
00:06:59,541 --> 00:07:01,041
BUT LUCKILY I KNOW A SPELL THAT

123
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:02,750
SHOULD STOP HIM
BEFORE HE SUCCEEDS.

124
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:04,083
AT LEAST I HOPE IT WILL.

125
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:10,416
I SUPPOSE KINKEL WOULD
ENJOY MAKING MINDLESS SLAVES

126
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,208
DESTROY THEMSELVES FOR HIS
OWN SADISTIC AMUSEMENT.

127
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:15,708
- I KNEW THERE WAS SOMETHING
ABOUT THE COUNT I DIDN'T LIKE.

128
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,500
- RIGHT. SO LET'S GO
MAKE HIM PAY.

129
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:21,875
- Seiji: IS IT TOO LATE
TO CHANGE MY MIND?

130
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:23,500
- I GUESS NOT. BUT IF YOU DID

131
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,208
YOU'D HAVE TO LOAN
ME YOUR CAR, YOU KNOW.

132
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:26,875
- WELL, IF THAT'S THE
CASE, KOUHEI, NEVER MIND.

133
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,458
I'VE SEEN WHAT YOU CALL DRIVING.

134
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,416
- HEY, KNOCK IT OFF, YOU'RE
GONNA GET IN TROUBLE

135
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,666
IF YOU SCUFF UP THOSE SEATS.

136
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,000
BESIDES, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE FUN

137
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,208
WHILE YOUR MASTER'S
IN THE TRUNK.

138
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:36,000
YOU'LL JUST MAKE HER
FEEL WORSE.

139
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:38,291
- SHOWS HOW MUCH
YOU KNOW, SLAVE BOY.

140
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:40,125
MASTER TOLD ME SHE DOESN'T MIND
RIDING IN THE TRUNK

141
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:41,625
AS LONG AS IT'S NICE
AND CLEAN LIKE SEIJI'S

142
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:43,833
AND NOT OLD AND STINKY
LIKE YOURS IS.

143
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:45,500
- ( scoffs )

144
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,791
- I HATE THAT HIROMI
AND THE EDITOR-IN-CHIEF

145
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:00,291
HAD TO GET MIXED
UP IN ALL OF THIS.

146
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:03,333
I CAN'T HELP
BUT FEEL RESPONSIBLE.

147
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,500
- THAT'S ONE MORE REASON
WHY WE NEED TO DO SOMETHING!

148
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:09,083
- RIGHT?
- YEAH.

149
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,583
- ( lightning crashing )

150
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,916
- THAT'S WEIRD. THE
LAST TIME WE WERE HERE,

151
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,833
THE PLACE LOOKED CONDEMNED.

152
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:31,458
- I SUPPOSE HE WANTED TO MAKE IT
MORE SUITABLE FOR HIS GUESTS.

153
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,500
- YOU MEAN MORE SUITABLE
FOR HIS VICTIMS.

154
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:39,166
HEY, WHAT'S WITH THE BACKPACK?

155
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:42,000
- I FOUND IT IN THE STOREROOM.
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S CUTE?

156
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:45,416
- KILL ME, PLEASE.

157
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:49,166
- I'M WILLING TO BET IT'S
MORE THAN DECORATIVE. SEE?

158
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,916
STAKES, CROSSES,
GARLIC, HOLY WATER.

159
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,333
THESE THINGS COULD
COME IN HANDY,

160
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,166
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING
OUR ADVERSARY.

161
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:57,333
SHE'S ACTUALLY PLANNING AHEAD.

162
00:08:57,416 --> 00:08:58,708
- WELL, IF THEY'RE SO
FRICKING HANDY,

163
00:08:58,791 --> 00:09:01,208
HOW COME LITTLE MISS
BLOODSUCKER HERE ISN'T AFFECTED?

164
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,625
- WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO KNOW?

165
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:05,208
- IT'S PROBABLY 'CAUSE
YOUR SKIN'S THICK AS A RHINO'S.

166
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,333
- MY SKIN'S SOFT AS SILK,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH!

167
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,416
- ( gate creaking )

168
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,958
- ( all gasping )

169
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:22,041
- HIROMI, IS THAT YOU?

170
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,500
- MY MASTER HAS BEEN
EXPECTING YOU.

171
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:29,958
- ( thunder rumbling )

172
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,208
- PLEASE FEEL FREE TO
ENJOY SOME REFRESHMENTS.

173
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:50,541
- YUM! DON'T HAVE TO
ASK ME TWICE!

174
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:52,833
- HEY, WHAT IF THE FOOD'S
POISONOUS OR SOMETHING?

175
00:09:52,916 --> 00:09:56,375
MAYBE SUPERNATURAL THINGS
LIKE SHIKIGAMI ARE IMMUNE TO IT.

176
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:57,791
- I BELIEVE POISON IS A LITTLE

177
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,750
TOO OBVIOUS FOR
THE COUNT'S TASTE.

178
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,416
I GET THE FEELING
THIS IS HIS VERSION

179
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,833
OF THE LAST SUPPER
BEFORE OUR CRUCIFIXION.

180
00:10:11,458 --> 00:10:15,333
- YOUR SOUP HAS GOTTEN COLD.
SHALL I REHEAT IT?

181
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:17,500
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME BREAD
TO GO WITH YOUR MEAL?

182
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:19,625
I COULD BUTTER IT.

183
00:10:19,708 --> 00:10:21,416
PERHAPS YOU WOULD LIKE
SOME ROASTED MEAT?

184
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,125
I COULD CUT IT FOR YOU.

185
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,208
AND THIS ONE'S THE SOY SAUCE,

186
00:10:29,291 --> 00:10:31,625
SO MAKE SURE YOU DON'T
MIX THEM UP, OKAY?

187
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:33,375
HERE YOU GO, HAZUKI,
YOUR FIRST COMMISSION.

188
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:36,625
HEY? WHAT'S WITH THE SAD FACE?

189
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:38,666
I GO TO ALL THIS TROUBLE
FOR MY CUTE LITTLE FRIEND,

190
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,083
DESPITE MY INSANE WORK SCHEDULE,

191
00:10:40,166 --> 00:10:42,208
AND SHE JUST LOOKS AT ME
LIKE I'VE RIPPED HER HEART OUT.

192
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:46,708
- HIROMI, ARE YOU
STILL IN THERE?

193
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:49,333
- WOULD MISTRESS LUNA
PREFER DESSERT INSTEAD?

194
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:50,708
- ( crackling )

195
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:52,041
- ( gasps )

196
00:10:52,125 --> 00:10:54,333
- YOUR GRANDFATHER
TASTED THIS DESSERT AS WELL.

197
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:56,541
I HOPE YOU ENJOY IT,
IT'S MY SPECIALTY.

198
00:10:58,208 --> 00:11:00,583
- HIROMI!
- BIG SISTER!

199
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:16,833
I'LL GET YOU BACK TO NORMAL.

200
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:19,125
I PROMISE I WILL, HIROMI.
JUST HOLD ON!

201
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:28,875
- WHAT THE HELL?
WHY DID SHE HURT HERSELF?

202
00:11:28,958 --> 00:11:30,958
- I TOLD YOU. THAT'S THE WAY
THE COUNT OPERATES.

203
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:32,791
- MONSTER.

204
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:37,583
( gasps )

205
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:42,208
- PLEASE FOLLOW ME THIS WAY.
MY MASTER IS WAITING.

206
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:57,541
- MAN. DIDN'T LOOK THIS BIG
FROM THE OUTSIDE.

207
00:11:57,625 --> 00:11:59,458
SO, YOU REALLY
USED TO LIVE HERE, BRAT?

208
00:11:59,541 --> 00:12:00,583
- MMM-HMM.

209
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:06,833
- SEIJI, HAVE YOU BEEN ABLE
TO SENSE WHERE GRANDPA IS YET?

210
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:09,666
- SORT OF. I CAN TELL HE'S NEAR.

211
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:12,791
BUT FOR SOME REASON I'M NOT ABLE
TO PINPOINT HIS EXACT LOCATION.

212
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:23,083
- WHAT IS IT, HAZUKI?
- OH, IT'S NOTHING.

213
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:34,791
- PLEASE MAKE
YOURSELVES COMFORTABLE.

214
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,375
- NO! DON'T GO, HIROMI!

215
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:44,541
- YOU GOT WHAT YOU WANTED,
NOW SHOW YOURSELF KINKEL!

216
00:12:44,625 --> 00:12:46,708
WHERE'S MY GRANDFATHER, DAMN IT?

217
